This paper deals with the analysis of research funding systems, which involves the use of data extraction and coding techniques. This is a common theme in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social informatics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of funding data for strategic intelligence applications, which could be relevant to the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
